-- A civil jury found former American football star O.J. Simpson liable for the wrongful death of his ex-wife and her friend.
ANGELES (AP) -- There is no agreement yet on the custody of O.J. Simpson's younger children. Lou Brown, the father of Simpson's slain ex-wife, said.'' Simpson's lawyer, Bernard Leckie, told The Associated Press that an agreement giving custody to Simpson was ready to be signed. ``I don't know why the attorney was discussing it,'. ``It's supposed to be confidential.'' Brown's lawyer did not return a phone call seeking comment. Simpson was out of town and couldn't be reached.
